results.name: Highest minimal Lee distance of any Type 4^Z self-dual code of length n over Z/4Z which does not have all Euclidean norms divisible by 8, that is, is strictly Type I. Compare A105681.
link: S. T. Dougherty, M. Harada and P. Solé, Shadow Codes over Z_4, Finite Fields Applic., 7 (2001), 507-529.
G. Nebe, E. M. Rains and N. J. A. Sloane, Self-Dual Codes and Invariant Theory, Springer, Berlin, 2006.
E. M. Rains and N. J. A. Sloane, Self-dual codes, pp. 177-294 of Handbook of Coding Theory, Elsevier, 1998; (Abstract, pdf, ps).
xref: Cf. A066013 for number of codes. See also A066014-A066017.
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Dec 11 2001
